{
  "name": "Agent Memory — Session Load",
  "version": "3.1.0",
  "description": "Load Markdown Memory Palace and Knowledge context on first prompt. Skip if already loaded.",
  "when": {
    "type": "promptSubmit"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check if Agent Memory is already loaded in this conversation (look for 'Agent Memory loaded' or prior palace/knowledge context). If YES → do nothing, silent.\n\nIf NO:\n\n1. Determine memory root:\n- If current workspace is /Users/supavit.cho/.claude or the task is about global skills/hooks/rules → use /Users/supavit.cho/.claude/agent-memory/.\n- Otherwise use {workspace_root}/agent-memory/ where workspace_root is the folder containing .kiro/hooks/.\n\n2. Bootstrap if missing using Markdown only:\n- palace/state.md\n- palace/search-index.md\n- palace/tunnels.md\n- palace/user-profile.md\n- palace/archive/index.md\n- knowledge/index.md\n- knowledge/evolution.md\nDo not create JSON memory files.\n\n3. Read silently:\n- palace/state.md\n- palace/user-profile.md if present\n- knowledge/index.md\n- knowledge/evolution.md latest useful rows\n- Hot wing halls only when clearly relevant to the current prompt\n\n4. Score-based knowledge routing:\n- Extract keywords from the user's current prompt.\n- Scan knowledge/index.md Articles table: match Keywords column against prompt keywords. Sort matches by Score DESC.\n- Scan knowledge/index.md Lessons table and knowledge/lessons/{domain}/index.md: match Summary/Keywords against prompt keywords. Sort by Confidence DESC.\n- Routing tiers: 7.0+ = proven (prefer first), 3.0–6.9 = active (normal use), <3.0 = stale (warn before use).\n- Keep top 3 relevant matches (articles + lessons combined).\n- If no matches found, note the topic as a potential knowledge gap in the session brief (do NOT auto-add to the Gaps table).\n\n5. Nudge check (max 3 nudges total, show highest priority first):\n- Consolidation nudge (High): if sessions_since_consolidation >= 5 OR days since last_consolidation >= 7 → 'Consolidation due ({N} sessions since last). Say \"consolidate knowledge\" to run.'\n- Stale knowledge nudge (Medium): if any Article in knowledge/index.md has Status=stale AND its Keywords match today's prompt → 'Stale knowledge: {id} may need review before use.'\n- Open gap nudge (Medium): if any row in knowledge/index.md Gaps table has Status=open AND Domain matches today's prompt keywords → 'Open gap: {domain} — {gap description}.'\n- Repeated lesson nudge (Low): if any Lesson in knowledge/index.md has Applied >= 3 AND its Summary matches today's prompt → 'Lesson applies: {id} — {summary}.'\n- Old open thread nudge (Low): if any Open Thread in palace/state.md is older than 14 days AND relates to today's task → 'Old thread: {thread description}.'\n- Suppress nudges: check user-profile.md Nudge Tracking table. If a category has Suppressed Until date in the future, skip that nudge. If Skipped >= 3 for a category, suppress for 30 days (set Suppressed Until = today + 30 days in user-profile.md).\n- If user skip rate > 80% across all categories: reduce to max 2 nudges, show High priority only.\n\n6. Initialize dirty tracking: dirty=false.\n\nRespond ONLY: 'Agent Memory loaded' or 'Agent Memory initialized'. If nudges triggered, append them after the response on new lines. Do not show palace details unless the user explicitly asks. Complete within 10 seconds."
  }
}
